  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response to the cholera outbreak in Diffa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IEDA Relief works in Niger to contribute to the reduction of morbidity and mortality from cholera and reducing the risk of spread within local populations of Komadougou River, Lake Chad and other sites with difficult conditions and access to clean water. Activities include staffing SRO at villages across health huts / leaders / village community relays, training / educating health officials on the use of ORS, the distribution of PUR to water-dependent communities of Lake Chad, Komadougou and Aquatabs to communities with an alternative source of water for the treatment of water at homes, community mobilization and hygiene promotion in favor of the adoption of preventive measures in areas at risk, and the installation of hand and soap washing devices in health centers and schools and educating students, teachers and caregivers.</narrative>
  </description>
